author: John Kennedy
title: Florida redistricting: Legislature's special session collapses
text:
Deadlocked by dueling ideas and egos, Florida’s House and Senate failed to agree on a new congressional map Friday, ending a costly, 12-day special session amid a flurry of icy exchanges.
The collapse raised the prospect that the Florida Supreme Court will soon step in to craft boundaries for the state’s 27 congressional districts. The special session was forced after justices last month overturned the Legislature’s latest attempt at drawing lines.
